  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Staff Application Engineer",
  "description": "<p>The incumbent is responsible to provide pre-sales and post-sales application support to customer on semiconductor testing activities and requirements, maintain customer  satisfaction so as to maintain or become the preferred tester platform. <br /></p><p><strong>Job responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Project management, delivery and support of Test Program/Test Library  creation, conversion or consultation as required by Customer</li><li>Provide support and consultation for Hardware and Software solutions for Customer Projects and Production requirements</li><li>Post sales consulting and support including Test methodology creation, enhancements and modifications, test hardware/ software feature recommendations and audit</li><li>Support and debug production issues such as correlation, test time and yield discrepancy, RTE, hang-ups etc</li><li>Delivery of application training, knowledge transfer and skill-up for Customer</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Required skills:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor's Degree or Master's Degree in Electrical and Electronic Engineering or equivalent</li><li>Minimum 10-15 years of working experience in IC testing industry, knowledge on 93000 software is a must</li><li>Good knowledge of Digital/Mixed signal test methodologies</li><li>Well versed with Java and C++, script programming, knowledge on debugging tools will be an added advantage</li><li>Good experience in test program development and test floor exposures</li><li>Strong problem solver with good technical capabilities, good communication skill, self-motivated, customer focus and result oriented</li><li>Ability to work independently with minimum supervision</li><li>Open to occasional travel with short notice to support escalation</li></ul>",
